What Changed From v1 (And Why)
The original plan was production-enterprise grade. Impressive, but designed for a 6-month paid engineering team. Here's what was cut and what replaced it:

Original	Replaced With	Why
AWS ECS Fargate (~$10/mo)	Render.com free tier	Free, Docker-native, zero config
AWS RDS (~$15/mo)	Supabase free tier (PostgreSQL)	Free, 500 MB, managed, has a dashboard
AWS ALB (~$16/mo)	Handled by Render automatically	No cost, HTTPS included
AWS NAT Gateway (~$32/mo)	Not needed	Biggest single cost eliminated
Terraform	Removed (optional bonus)	Overkill for 8 weeks; adds a week of setup
AWS WAF	Rate limiting in Express + Render DDoS protection	WAF costs money; Express rate limiting is free
AWS Secrets Manager	Render environment variables + .env files	Free, built into the platform
AWS CloudTrail	Not needed	Enterprise audit tool; irrelevant at this scale
6 sprints Г— 2 weeks	4 sprints Г— 2 weeks	Keeps momentum, still ships a real product
Staging + Production environments	One deployed environment	Two environments doubles the work for no learning benefit here
Redis / ElastiCache	Not needed	No feature in this project requires a cache
Multi-AZ RDS	Not applicable	Using Supabase which handles this
