Authentication
[ ] POST /api/v1/auth/register:
Validate body with Zod (email, password min 8 chars, full_name)
Check email not already taken (return 409 if so)
Hash password with bcrypt (10 salt rounds)
Create user in DB
Issue access token (15 min) and refresh token (7 days)
Store refresh token hash in DB
Return { accessToken, user: { id, email, fullName, role } }
[ ] POST /api/v1/auth/login:
Validate body
Look up user by email (return 401 if not found вҖ” don't say "email not found")
Compare password with bcrypt
Issue new tokens, store refresh token hash
Return same shape as register
[ ] POST /api/v1/auth/refresh:
Read refresh token from request body (or httpOnly cookie вҖ” team's choice)
Hash it, look up in DB, check not expired
Delete old token, issue new tokens (rotation)
Return new access token
[ ] POST /api/v1/auth/logout:
Require valid access token
Delete refresh token from DB
Return 204
[ ] GET /api/v1/auth/me:
Require valid access token
Return current user profile
