10. Security Plan (Simplified)
All the same security principles as v1, implemented with simpler tools.

What's Handled Automatically By The Platform
HTTPS: Both Vercel and Render provide HTTPS with auto-renewing TLS certificates. You do nothing except not break it.
DDoS protection: Both platforms have basic DDoS mitigation built in.
What You Implement in Express (Abdul + You)
Security headers (one line, helmet npm package):

import helmet from 'helmet';
app.use(helmet()); // Sets X-Frame-Options, X-Content-Type-Options, Strict-Transport-Security, etc.
CORS (restricted to frontend origin):

import cors from 'cors';
app.use(cors({
  origin: process.env.ALLOWED_ORIGIN,  // e.g. https://your-app.vercel.app
  credentials: true
}));
Rate limiting:

import rateLimit from 'express-rate-limit';

// Global: 100 requests per minute per IP
app.use(rateLimit({ windowMs: 60_000, max: 100 }));

// Auth routes: 10 requests per minute per IP
const authLimiter = rateLimit({ windowMs: 60_000, max: 10 });
app.use('/api/v1/auth/login', authLimiter);
app.use('/api/v1/auth/register', authLimiter);
Input validation (Zod, on every route):

// Example route with validation middleware
router.post('/tasks', authenticate, validate(createTaskSchema), createTask);

// Validation middleware
function validate(schema: ZodSchema) {
  return (req, res, next) => {
    const result = schema.safeParse(req.body);
    if (!result.success) {
      return res.status(400).json({ error: { code: 'VALIDATION_ERROR', details: result.error.errors } });
    }
    req.body = result.data;
    next();
  };
}
Password hashing:

// Always bcrypt, never MD5/SHA, never store plaintext
const hash = await bcrypt.hash(password, 10);
const isValid = await bcrypt.compare(password, storedHash);
JWT token security:

Access tokens: 15-minute expiry, signed with JWT_SECRET
Refresh tokens: 7-day expiry, opaque random string hashed before DB storage, single-use rotation
Never put sensitive data in the JWT payload (no passwords, no payment info)
Ownership checks on every resource operation:

// Before updating or deleting a task:
const task = await prisma.task.findUnique({ where: { id } });
if (!task) return res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not found' });
if (task.ownerId !== req.user.id && req.user.role !== 'ADMIN') {
  return res.status(403).json({ error: 'Forbidden' });
}
What Himal Verifies (Security Review in Sprint 3)
Go through each endpoint and check:

[ ] Is the endpoint protected by the JWT middleware? (Try calling it without a token вҖ” should get 401)
[ ] Is the RBAC correct? (Try calling an admin endpoint as a regular user вҖ” should get 403)
[ ] Can a user access another user's resources? (Try calling /tasks/:id with a task owned by a different user вҖ” should get 403)
[ ] Does the endpoint validate its input? (Send an empty body вҖ” should get 400, not 500)
[ ] Does the error response leak internal details? (A 500 error should not return a stack trace)
